cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image super-resolution using deep learning techniques. The use of 3D convolution and spectral-spatial residual module also suggests that it may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of hyperspectral images may also make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
